{
  "macro_id": "mail.send",
  "domain": "mail",
  "name": "send",
  "inputs": {
    "toUserId": { "type": "string", "required": true, "maxLength": 128 },
    "subject": { "type": "string", "required": true, "maxLength": 120 },
    "body": { "type": "string", "maxLength": 4000 },
    "attachmentCc": { "type": "number", "min": 0 },
    "codCc": { "type": "number", "min": 0 }
  },
  "invariants": [
    "typeof output === 'object' && output !== null",
    "typeof output.ok === 'boolean'",
    "output.ok === false || (typeof output.id === 'string' && output.id.indexOf('mail_') === 0)",
    "output.ok === true || typeof output.error === 'string'"
  ],
  "fuzz_cases": [
    { "input": { "toUserId": "", "subject": "Hi" }, "expect": { "ok": false } },
    { "input": { "toUserId": "u2", "subject": "" }, "expect": { "ok": false } },
    { "input": { "toUserId": "assassin:mail.send", "subject": "self" }, "expect": { "ok": false, "error": "cannot_mail_self" } }
  ],
  "_note": "send runs under the assassin's live DB + internal actor (fromUserId = 'assassin:mail.send'). Case 1 → missing_users (empty toUserId); case 2 → subject_required (empty subject); case 3 → cannot_mail_self (toUserId equals the actor id). A non-self toUserId with a valid subject would SUCCEED (ok:true) — only the self-send is a guaranteed rejection without seeding recipient rows."
}
